ui.name: Representation
ui.doc: Choose the type for the representation.

ui.name: Map Scalars
ui.doc:
When set to True, LookupTable will always be
        used for scalar mapping. Otherwise, when up to 4 component
        scalars are present, the components are clamped to a valid
        color interval (0-255 for an integral type and 0.0-1.0 for a
        floating point type) and then directly used as
        color.

ui.name: Interpolate Scalars Before Mapping
ui.doc:
When set to true (default), texture coordinates
        are sent to and interpolated by the graphics card. This is
        equivalent with interpolating scalars and then mapping them to
        obtain colors between points. Otherwise, colors are sent to
        and interpolated by the graphics card.

ui.name: Edge Color
ui.doc:
Set the edge color. This color is used to draw the edge
        for the polygonal data when EdgeVisibility is on.

ui.name: Backface Representation
ui.doc:
Choose the representation type for the
        backface.

ui.name: Triangulate
ui.doc:
Triangulate the geometry internally to avoid rendering
        issues of non-convex polygons. This feature has a processing and memory
        cost, it should be enabled only when needed.

ui.name: Block Colors Distinct Values
ui.doc:
Determines the number of distinct values in
          vtkBlockColors. This array is added to each block if
          the dataset is a composite dataset. The array has one value
          set to (blockIndex % BlockColorsDistinctValues)

ui.name: Use Data Partitions
ui.doc:
Specify whether or not to redistribute the data when actor is translucent.
        Default is false.

ui.name: OSPRay Use Scale Array
ui.doc: Allows OSPRay implicit points and lines to be sized by an array.

ui.name: OSPRay Scale Array
ui.doc: Choice of an array for OSPRay implicit points and lines sizes.

ui.name: OSPRay Scale Function
ui.doc:
Set the piecewise function used to map data array to sprite size.
        ScaleTransferFunction is only used if ScaleByArray is set.

ui.name: Orient
ui.doc:
If this property is set to 1, the glyphs will be
        oriented based on the selected orientation vector
        array.

ui.name: Orientation Mode
ui.doc:
Orientation mode indicates if the OrientationArray
        provides the direction vector for the orientation or the rotations
        around each axes. Default is DIRECTION.

ui.name: Scaling
ui.doc:
Enable/Disable scaling of source
        geometry.

ui.name: Scale Factor
ui.doc:
The value of this property will be used as a multiplier
        for scaling the glyphs before adding them to the
        output.

ui.name: Glyph Type
ui.doc: Specify the source objects.

ui.name: Use Glyph Table
ui.doc:
When true, the glyph data is expected to be a multiblock
        dataset, where each top-level node contains a separate glyph which may
        be selected by a point data array on the input dataset.

ui.name: Use Composite Glyph Table
ui.doc:
When true, the glyph data is expected to be a multiblock
        dataset, where each top-level node contains a separate glyph which may
        be selected by a point data array on the input dataset.

children.name: Grid Axes Visibility
children.doc: Used for the checkbox in the UI.

children.name: X Title
children.doc: Set the title string for X axis.

children.name: Y Title
children.doc: Set the title string for Y axis.

children.name: Z Title
children.doc: Set the title string for Z axis.

children.name: Faces To Render
children.doc:
Set the mask to select faces. The faces rendered will be a subset of the
          faces selected depending on the status of **CullBackface** and
          **CullFrontface** properties.

children.name: Cull Backface
children.doc:
Set to true to hide faces of the grid facing away from the camera i.e. hide all
              back faces.

children.name: Cull Frontface
children.doc:
Set to true to hide faces of the grid facing towards from the camera i.e. hide all
              front faces.

children.name: Grid Color
children.doc: Color used when coloring the grid wireframe

children.name: Show Grid
children.doc: Turn off to not render the plane grids.

children.name: Show Edges
children.doc: Turn off to not render the plane edges.

children.name: Show Ticks
children.doc: Turn off to not render the tick marks.

children.name: Label Unique Edges Only
children.doc:
Set to true to only label edges shared with 1 face. Note that
          if all faces are being rendered, this will generate no labels.

children.name: Axes To Label
children.doc:
Set the mask to select the axes to label. The axes labelled will be a subset of the
          axes selected depending on which faces are also being rendered.

children.name: X Axis Notation
children.doc: Get/set the numerical notation, standard, scientific or mixed (0, 1, 2) for X Axis.

children.name: X Axis Precision
children.doc: Get/set the numerical precision to use for the X Axis, default is 2.

children.name: X Axis Use Custom Labels
children.doc:
Specify whether to use custom labels for the X axis. Labels
          specified by **XAxisLabels** are used only when
          this flag is set to 1.

children.name: Y Axis Notation
children.doc: Get/set the numerical notation, standard, scientific or mixed (0, 1, 2) for Y Axis.

children.name: Y Axis Precision
children.doc: Get/set the numerical precision to use for the Y Axis, default is 2.

children.name: Y Axis Use Custom Labels
children.doc:
Specify whether to use custom labels for the Y axis. Labels
          specified by **YAxisLabels** are used only when
          this flag is set to 1.

children.name: Z Axis Notation
children.doc: Get/set the numerical notation, standard, scientific or mixed (0, 1, 2) for Z Axis.

children.name: Z Axis Precision
children.doc: Get/set the numerical precision to use for the Z Axis, default is 2.

children.name: Z Axis Use Custom Labels
children.doc:
Specify whether to use custom labels for the Z axis. Labels
          specified by **ZAxisLabels** are used only when
          this flag is set to 1.

ui.name: Visibility
ui.doc: Set the visibility of the representation.

ui.name: Translation
ui.doc: Set the polar axes origin position.

ui.name: Scale
ui.doc: Set the polar axes bounds transform scale.

ui.name: Orientation
ui.doc: Set the polar axes bounds transform orientation.

ui.name: Enable Custom Bounds
ui.doc: Activate the use of polar axes custom bounds.

ui.name: Custom Bounds
ui.doc: Set the polar axes custom bounds.

ui.name: Enable Custom Range
ui.doc: Activate the use of polar axes custom range.

ui.name: Custom Range
ui.doc: Set the polar axes custom range.

ui.name: Polar Axis Visibility
ui.doc: Set the visibility of polar axis.

ui.name: Radial Axes Visibility
ui.doc: Set all radial axes visibility.

ui.name: Draw Radial Gridlines
ui.doc: Set the visibility of radial grid lines.

ui.name: Polar Arcs Visibility
ui.doc: Set all polar arcs visibility.

ui.name: Draw Polar Arcs Gridlines
ui.doc: Set the visibility of polar arcs grid lines.

ui.name: Number Of Radial Axes
ui.doc:
Set the number of radial axes,
        If value is 0 (the default), the number of radial axes is automatically calculated.

ui.name: Auto Subdivide Polar Axis
ui.doc:
Automatically compute the number of
        polar axis ticks and tick size. If true, will override NumberOfPolarAxisTicks,
        PolarAxisMajorTickSize, LastRadialAxisMajorTickSize, ArcMajorTickSize properties.

ui.name: Number Of Polar Axis
ui.doc:
Set the number of polar axis and of course polar axis ticks,
        If value is 0 (the default), the number of polar axis tick
        is automatically calculated.
        ignored if AutoSubdividePolarAxis is true.

ui.name: Minimum Radius
ui.doc: Set the minimum radius, Maximum radius is automatically computed.

ui.name: Minimum Angle
ui.doc: Set the minimum angle.

ui.name: Maximum Angle
ui.doc: Set the maximum angle.

ui.name: Radial Axes Origin To Polar Axis
ui.doc:
If On, the radial axes are drawn from the angle of the polar Axis
        (i.e. MinimumAngle) and continue counterclockwise with the step DeltaAngleRadialAxes.
        if Off, the start angle is 0.0.

ui.name: Ratio
ui.doc: Set the polar ellipse ratio.

ui.name: Polar Axis Color
ui.doc: Set the Polar Axis color.

ui.name: Polar Arcs Color
ui.doc: Set the Polar Arcs color.

ui.name: Last Radial Axis Color
ui.doc: Set the Last Radial Axis color.

ui.name: Secondary Polar Arcs Color
ui.doc: Set the Secondary Polar Arcs color.

ui.name: Secondary Radial Axes Color
ui.doc: Set the Secondary Radial Axes color.

ui.name: Polar Axis Title Visibility
ui.doc: Set the visibility of polar axis title.

ui.name: Polar Axis Title
ui.doc: Set the polar axis title.

ui.name: Polar Axis Title Location
ui.doc: Set the location of polar axis title.

ui.name: Polar Label Visibility
ui.doc: Set the visibility of polar axis label.

ui.name: Polar Label Format
ui.doc: Set the polar axis label format.

ui.name: Polar Label Exponent Location
ui.doc: Set the location of exponent.

ui.name: Radial Label Visibility
ui.doc: Set radial label visibility.

ui.name: Radial Label Format
ui.doc: Set the polar radial label format.

ui.name: Radial Label Location
ui.doc: Set the location of radial labels.

ui.name: Radial Units Visibility
ui.doc: Show radial units in labels (degrees).

ui.name: Screen Size
ui.doc:
Set the screen size to use, which impact label and title
        relative location to the axes.

ui.name: Enable Distance LOD
ui.doc: Set the use of LOD based on distance.

ui.name: Distance LODThreshold
ui.doc: Set the LOD distance threshold to use.

ui.name: Enable View Angle LOD
ui.doc: Set the use of LOD based on the View Angle.

ui.name: View Angle LODThreshold
ui.doc: Set the LOD View Angle threshold to use.

ui.name: Smallest Visible Polar Angle
ui.doc: Set the smallest radial angle distinguishable from polar axis.

ui.name: Polar Ticks Visibility
ui.doc: Set all ticks visibility.

ui.name: Arc Ticks Origin To Polar Axis
ui.doc:
If On, the ticks are drawn from the angle of the polar Axis
        (MinimumAngle) and continue counterclockwise with the step Delta Angle Major/Minor.
        If Off, the start angle is 0.0

ui.name: Tick Location
ui.doc: Set the location of ticks.

ui.name: Axis Tick Visibility
ui.doc: Set polar axis and last radial axis tick visibility.

ui.name: Axis Minor Tick Visibility
ui.doc: Set polar axis and last radial axis minor tick visibility.

ui.name: Arc Tick Visibility
ui.doc: Set polar arc tick visibility.

ui.name: Arc Minor Tick Visibility
ui.doc: Set polar arc minor tick visibility.

ui.name: Delta Angle Major
ui.doc: Set the delta between major ticks on last arc.

ui.name: Delta Angle Minor
ui.doc: Set the delta between minor and major ticks on last arc.

ui.name: Polar Axis Major Tick Size
ui.doc:
Set the polar axis major tick size,
        If value is 0 (the default), tick size is automatically calculated.

ui.name: Polar Axis Tick Ratio Size
ui.doc: Set the polar axis size ratio between major and minor ticks.

ui.name: Polar Axis Major Tick Thickness
ui.doc: Set the thickness of polar axis major ticks.

ui.name: Polar Axis Tick Ratio Thickness
ui.doc: Set the thickness ratio between major and minor ticks of polar axis.

ui.name: Last Radial Axis Major Tick Size
ui.doc:
Set the last radial axis major tick size,
        If value is 0 (the default), tick size is automatically calculated.

ui.name: Last Radial Axis Tick Ratio Size
ui.doc: Set the last radial axis size ratio between major and minor ticks.

ui.name: Last Radial Axis Major Tick Thickness
ui.doc: Set the thickness of last radial axis major ticks.

ui.name: Last Radial Axis Tick Ratio Thickness
ui.doc: Set the thickness ratio between major and minor ticks of last radial axis.

ui.name: Arc Major Tick Size
ui.doc:
Set the arc major tick size,
        If value is 0 (the default), tick size is automatically calculated.

ui.name: Arc Tick Ratio Size
ui.doc: Set the arc size ratio between major and minor ticks.

ui.name: Arc Major Tick Thickness
ui.doc: Set the thickness of arc major ticks.

ui.name: Arc Tick Ratio Thickness
ui.doc: Set the thickness ratio between major and minor ticks of arc.

ui.name: Use 2D Mode
ui.doc: Set the use of 2D Mode for all axes.

ui.name: Use Log Axis
ui.doc: Set the use of Log axis.

ui.name: Select Mapper
ui.doc:
Select the volume mapper to use for Volume
        rendering.

ui.name: Sampling Dimensions
ui.doc: How many linear samples we want along each axis

ui.name: Use Floating Point Frame Buffer
ui.doc:
Enable use of floating point frame buffers. If not enabled,
          you may encounter artifacts when mixing volumes with geometry.

ui.name: Gaussian Radius
ui.doc: The radius of the gaussian blur for each point.

ui.name: Emissive
ui.doc: Should the splat be emissive lke a light source or not. For cosmology emissive should be on. For scanned point clouds typically it woudl be off.

ui.name: Use Scale Array
ui.doc:
If this property is on, the Scale Array will be used to determine that radii
          of the gaussians.  Otherwise the Default Radius will be used.

ui.name: Gaussian Scale Array
ui.doc: This property specifies the name of the input array to scale the splats by.

ui.name: Scale Transfer Function
ui.doc:
Set the piecewise function used to map data array to sprite size.
        ScaleTransferFunction is only used if ScaleByArray is set.

ui.name: Use Opacity Array
ui.doc:
If this property is on, the Opacity Array will be used to determine the
          point gaussian sprites.

ui.name: Gaussian Opacity Array
ui.doc: This property specifies the name of the input array to map to point opacity.

ui.name: Opacity Transfer Function
ui.doc:
Set the piecewise function used to map data array to sprite opacity.
        OpacityTransferFunction is only used if ScaleByArray is set and OpacityArray is
        also given.
